<paragraph blockId="20.[151,741,1198,1224]" box="[151,741,1198,1224]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,741,1198,1224]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,741,1198,1224]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1889" box="[287,515,1198,1224]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Thaumetopoeinae">Thaumetopoeinae</taxonomicName>
* Aurivillius, 1889
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,1269,1402]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
*Miller (1911) concluded 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1889" box="[463,663,1269,1294]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Thaumetopoeinae">Thaumetopoeinae</taxonomicName>
to be a subfamily under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1829" box="[980,1136,1269,1294]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Notodontidae</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Schintlmeister, A." pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="1 - 605" refId="ref50411" refString="Schintlmeister, A. (2013) Notodontidae &amp; Oenosandridae (Lepidoptera). In: World Catalogue of Insects. Vol. 11. Brill, Leiden, pp. 1 - 605." type="book chapter" year="2013">Schintlmeister (2013)</bibRefCitation>
stated that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1889" box="[369,570,1305,1330]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Thaumetopoeinae">Thaumetopoeinae</taxonomicName>
stands phylogenetically somewhat far from the rest of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1829" box="[1277,1433,1305,1330]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Notodontidae</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kobayashi, H. &amp; Nonaka, M." box="[151,478,1341,1366]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref47178" refString="Kobayashi, H. &amp; Nonaka, M. (2016) Molecular Phylogeny of the Notodontidae: Subfamilies Inferred from 28 S rRNA Sequences (Lepidoptera, Noctuoidea, Notodontidae). Tinea, 23 (1), 1 - 83." type="journal article" year="2016">Kobayashi &amp; Nonaka (2016)</bibRefCitation>
after phylogenetic analysis confirmed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1889" box="[919,1120,1341,1366]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Thaumetopoeinae">Thaumetopoeinae</taxonomicName>
as a stable subfamily under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1829" box="[151,307,1377,1402]" class="Insecta" family="Notodontidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Notodontidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
